article.headline: Chicago St 64, Southern Utah 60
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- Royce Parran's 18 points, including three 3-pointers, led all scorers and helped lift Chicago State to a 64-60 win over Southern Utah on Thursday night. Michael Henderson added 13 points and grabbed eight rebounds for the Cougars (5-17, 4-7 Mid-Continent), who were outshot 44 percent to 41 percent for the game but scored 14 points off turnovers to Southern Utah's six. The Thunderbirds (7-17, 5-6) were led by 15 points from Henry Uhegwu, while Lubor Olsovsky scored 13 and snagged nine rebounds. Justin Allen added 10 points off the bench. Southern Utah shot nearly 62 percent from the field in the second half, but couldn't overcome a 31-26 halftime deficit.
